defaultThe 
defaultd
defaultepartment is encouraging 
defaultcouncils
default to open up their procurement to
default local firms but g
defaultovernment procurement is subject to Public Procurement Regulations 
default2006 
defaultand these prohibit any form of discrimination against compani
defaultes solely on the basis of their nationality
default within the European Economic Area
default and those countries which are signatories to the Government Procurement Agreement. I
defaultt would therefore be unlawful to seek to restrict artificially the num
defaultber of contracts awarded
default to non-
defaultUK based firms. It is similarly unlawful to seek to reserve a proportion of spend for UK based firms. These regulations are designed to ensure fair cross border trade, and they of course work both ways. The benefit for UK firms is that they are abl
defaulte to compete effectively and without unfai
defaultr prejudice against them in non-
defaultUK markets, especially within the E
defaulturopean Union
default. Other European countries are subject to the same regulations and for the same reasons
default.
