default The Fair Deal is a non-statutory policy setting out how pension issues are dealt with when staff are compulsorily transferred from the public sector to inde
defaultpendent providers delivering public services.  New Fair Deal guidance was issued by
default&#xa0;
defaultTreasury in October 2013
default&#xa0;
defaultand applies when staff who are members of a public service pension scheme move from the public sector to an independent contractor by way of a tran
defaultsfer to which TUPE applies, and when staff who are members of a public service pension scheme move by way of a non-voluntary transfer to a public service mutual or to other new models of public service delivery (regardless of whether or not TUPE applies).
